    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>2 Accounting Firms Plan a Merger</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mangini &amp; Co, certified public accounting firm in Armonk, NY, merges with Marshall Granger &amp; Co; new company, based in Armonk; will be named Marshall Granger CPAs and will be headed by Mangini managing partners Ronald J Mangini and Laurence M Brown (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mangini &amp; Co., an Armonk-based certified public accounting firm, is merging with the Tarrytown-based Marshall Granger &amp; Co. The new company will be based in Armonk and will be named Marshall Granger CPAs. It will be headed by the managing partners of Mangini &amp; Co., Ronald J. Mangini and Laurence M. Brown.</p>
        <p>Together, the firms have a staff of 10 certified public accountants and more than $2.5 million in annual billings.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
